3. acceptance criteria coverage

- Each shared Vue primitive now has a clearer review story with explicit state labels and broader coverage.
- Stories now go beyond happy paths where it matters: `loading`, `disabled`, `disabled-link`, `valid`, `invalid`, `prompt`, `with-actions`, `without-actions`, tone variants, padding variants, custom tab content, and tooltip placement review.
- Histoire parity is tighter with HEEx because the stories now use the same review vocabulary already called out in `/dev/design-system`, especially `neutral`, `primary`, `success`, `warning`, `danger`, `valid`, `invalid`, `disabled`, and `loading`.
- Stable state names are now first-class in the stories through the new shared helpers in [review.ts](/Users/mhostetler/Source/EBoss/eboss_platform/apps/eboss_web/assets/vue/stories/review.ts) and [StoryStateCard.vue](/Users/mhostetler/Source/EBoss/eboss_platform/apps/eboss_web/assets/vue/stories/StoryStateCard.vue), which sets up later Vitest component-case naming.
- [UiTooltip.vue](/Users/mhostetler/Source/EBoss/eboss_platform/apps/eboss_web/assets/vue/components/ui/UiTooltip.vue) gained an `open` prop so tooltip review can include static placement states in Histoire instead of hover-only inspection.

4. blockers/assumptions

- `mix precommit` could not be left passing in this sandbox. First, Mix 1.19’s TCP-based PubSub is blocked here; second, database-backed test startup is blocked by sandbox socket permissions to Postgres, even when routed through the local Unix socket.
- I worked around the Mix PubSub issue with a temporary `/tmp` wrapper only to verify non-DB steps, but I did not change repository code to accommodate the sandbox.
- The repository changes for `ST-DSN-008` are complete; the remaining failure is environmental, not from the Vue/Histoire story implementation.
